MASTERS TOURNAMENT
April 6, 2007
Fuzzy Zoeller
START_OF_INTERVIEW_TEXT
 
 
  
 
  
  
   
  Q.  Talking about his round.   

 FUZZY ZOELLER:  I made a hell of a four on 18.   
  
  Q.  On lack of past champions on the leader board.   

 FUZZY ZOELLER:  Give it time, this is a four day tournament.   
  
  Q.  On course conditions.   

 FUZZY ZOELLER:  Greens on back nine are a lot different than on the front nine.   
  
  Q.  Talk about the weather and the temperature?   

 FUZZY ZOELLER:  Not bad, once we got rolling.   
  
  Q.  On chances of making the cut.   

 FUZZY ZOELLER:  All I care about is the sun rising in the morning.  The rest can take care of itself.   

 It's a battle, it's a challenge.   
   
  End of FastScripts   

END_OF_INTERVIEW_TEXT